result.name: 家外家 Take Homemade

reviews.text: A local restaurant serving Cantonese cuisine. Takeaway available.
Good soup good value

A nice quiet and not too big  place offering typical Hongkongese dishes, mostly quick eats, among them dim sum, scallion cake, rice with pork, radish cake. There is also a not too large range of beverages offered, among them soy bean milk. The place was not crowded in the afternoon, the staff was forthcoming, English was spoken. The interior is no frills but nice. There is a large table in the middle of the room and a long table along the window.
當你以為佢好健康啲飯溝咗藜麥，又有燉湯，點知啲排骨同义燒都充滿鬆肉粉，啲湯都好油，蒸蛋色又好橙味道唔多自然。

reviews.text: Breakfast is tasty. Convenient location. Not far away from Mid-Level Escalator.

Delifrance has some great afternoon tea packages! Do try their variety of croissants which they bake on the spot.
The staffs could be a bit more friendly. Lunch hours get busy so grab a table early if you are visiting for lunch.
Overpriced food court type pasta, only for those who wants to find a table to sit down for lunch instead in central
I realy don’t want act like Gorden Ramsey, but put a bit salt in the water before you cook pasta guys.
Very good food with good prices
